<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB8FFE2FF1CFC1B4B96F8D5" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FF1CFC1B4B06FB55" blockId="9.[113,765,972,1828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FF1CFC1B498CFC15" box="[151,238,973,996]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Notes. –</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FF7DFC1A48CAFC15" author="BURMAN" box="[246,424,972,996]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768)</bibRefCitation>
referred in the protologue to various pre-Linnaean publications and plates. He did not mention any collector, but “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FE14FBDA4B33FBD5" box="[415,593,1036,1060]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Habitat in Indiis</emphasis>
” as locality and the Javanese vernacular name “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FE48FBFA4B33FBB5" box="[451,593,1068,1092]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Daun-Peekou</emphasis>
”, which should be regarded as specimen citation (the only one in the protologue!), since this name is not mentioned in any of the cited publications, as stated by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FE0BFB5B4B02FB55" author="MERRILL" box="[384,608,1164,1188]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="334" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL (1921: 334)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FF1CFB7A4B9FF9F5" blockId="9.[113,765,972,1828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FF1CFB7A49C9FB35" box="[151,171,1196,1220]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">Asingle</collectionCode>
specimen in G-PREL [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FE60FB7A489CFB35" box="[491,510,1196,1220]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00818199] matches this citation; it bears the Javanese name “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FD8DFB1B4BE7FB15" box="[518,645,1228,1252]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Daun Pakoe</emphasis>
”, followed by two polynomials from the protologue and the name of the new species, all from Burman’s hand. Another specimen in G-PREL [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FF6FFAFA4995FAB5" box="[228,247,1324,1348]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00801097], possibly part of the original material, only bears the same two polynomials from an unknown hand. Three 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FF3DFABA482DFA75" box="[182,335,1388,1412]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paul Hermann</emphasis>
specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB8FFE2FD83FABA4B34FA75" box="[520,598,1388,1412]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
extant in BIF-CEYL (p. 152 (
<figureCitation id="49D32A11FFB8FFE2FE9DFA5A4837FA55" box="[278,341,1420,1444]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[136,164,1889,1908]" captionTargetBox="[332,1278,276,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[332,1278,276,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. – Page 152 of Paul Hermann’s herbarium from Ceylon in BIF-CEYL with the lectotype of Polypodium acutum Burm. f. (upper specimen) and original material of Polypodium palustre Burm. f. (lower specimen). [© Bibliothèque de l’Institut de France, Paris]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5684542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5684542/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, lower specimen), p. 21 and p. 156) may also be regarded as original material; they were used by Burman’s father for his 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FEC1FA1A4B41FA15" box="[330,547,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Thesaurus Zeylanicus</emphasis>
(1737), a work cited in the protologue (see above Notes under 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB8FFE2FDA2FA3A4B8CF9F5" box="[553,750,1516,1540]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FDA2FA3A4B8CF9F5" box="[553,750,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Polypodium acutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FF1CF9DA4B96F8D5" blockId="9.[113,765,972,1828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FF1CF9DA48F7F9D5" author="UNDERWOOD" box="[151,405,1548,1572]" firstAuthor="UNDERWOOD" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Torrey Bot. Club" page="38" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="35 - 50" part="33" refId="ref10337" refString="UNDERWOOD, L. M. (1906). The genus Stenochlaena. Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 33: 35 - 50." title="The genus Stenochlaena" type="journal article" year="1906">UNDERWOOD (1906: 38)</bibRefCitation>
cited the type specimen as “Type from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB8FFE2FF20F9FA499AF9B5" box="[171,248,1580,1604]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
”, and 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FEB2F9FA4BF8F9B5" author="FRASER-JENKINS" box="[313,666,1580,1604]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="FRASER-JENKINS" journalOrPublisher="Dehra Dun" page="187" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" refId="ref9233" refString="FRASER-JENKINS, C. R., K. N. GANDHI &amp; B. S. KHOLIA (2018). An Annotated Checklist of Indian Pteridophytes 2: Woodsiaceae to Dryopteridaceae. Dehra Dun." title="An Annotated Checklist of Indian Pteridophytes 2: Woodsiaceae to Dryopteridaceae" type="book" year="2018">FRASER-JENKINS et al. (2018: 187)</bibRefCitation>
as “Type from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB8FFE2FF20F99A4876F995" box="[171,276,1612,1636]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FEADF99B481FF995" box="[294,381,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">In Indiis</emphasis>
”, Herb. Burman,? 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FDCBF99A4B37F995" box="[576,597,1612,1636]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
”. None of these citations may be considered as valid implicit lectotypification, or even as first-step lectotypification, as 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FDACF95A4BB2F955" author="BURMAN" box="[551,720,1676,1700]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768)</bibRefCitation>
did not cite any specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB8FFE2FE16F97A4B6BF935" box="[413,521,1708,1732]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, and as there are three different gatherings from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB8FFE2FEF4F91A4885F915" box="[383,487,1740,1764]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
conserved in Paris. Therefore, we designate here the only specimen cited (G-PREL [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FFFCF8DA49E8F8D5" box="[119,138,1804,1828]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00818199]) as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB8FFE2FEA2F8DA48E8F8D5" box="[297,394,1804,1828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FE11F8DA4B1CF8D5" author="TURLAND" box="[410,638,1804,1828]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="TURLAND" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" refId="ref10318" refString="TURLAND, N. J., J. H. WIERSEMA, F. R. BARRIE, W. GREUTER, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, P. S. HERENDEEN, S. KNAPP, W. - H. KUSBER, D. - Z. LI, K. MARHOLD, T. W. MAY, J. MCNEILL, A. M. MONRO, J. PRADO, M. J. PRICE &amp; G. F. SMITH (2018). International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Veg. 159." title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="proceedings" year="2018">TURLAND et al., 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 9.12).
</paragraph>
